China is known for creating some of the world's tastiest and most unique cuisine - but not necessarily the quickest.

That is until a video emerged of one street trader creating one of the country's staple snacks in a matter of seconds.

The chef was filmed in Guangzhou, Guangdong province, rustling up the nice noodle rolls at lightning speed.

